body:
### Welcome to Techgroupmeetup on GitHub.
This repository is an easy way to keep informed of upcoming announcements. We provide consulting services for all of your projects. Contact us regarding your next idea here [Techgroupmeetup.com](https://techgroupmeetup.com), select a time to schedule a meeting, and we will be in touch. After your initial consultation, you can check out the project management case studies spanning 15 years in digital entertainment promotions. If you’re working on a business concept, simply connect with us and we can begin our journey together.

### Digital Media
We’ve pioneered award-winning methodologies for you to use. Go ahead and click 'Portfolio' to browse through them. You can easily launch a prototype before publishing your idea. Our team builds your project in conjunction with an eye on marketing and promoting to achieve your sales goals. After publishing your idea, you can improve your functionality via customer feedback in order to maximize ROI. Your ideas will be treated with respect and increased quality.

### Business Development
If you prefer to not waste time chasing the latest gimmick, encourage your team to create a strategic development plan. In addition to supporting day-to-day operations, Techgroupmeetup supports a variety of non-profits, a simple, SEO aware website workflow. Keely Grigel makes it easy to create innovative, quality ideas and profits without having to copy them from outdated industry trends. Techgroupmeetup also offers intelligent ecommerce website design and other advanced digital marketing features.

### Networking with Other Authors and Contributors
You can @mention any GitHub username, like @KeelyGrigel, to generate a link to their profile. The resulting `<a>` element will link to the contributor’s GitHub Profile. For example: In 2007, Chris Wanstrath (@defunkt), PJ Hyett (@pjhyett), and Tom Preston-Werner (@mojombo) founded GitHub.

### Support or Contact
Having trouble with organizing your ideas and leading your team project? Check out our [contact info](https://techgroupmeetup.com/contact) page and we’ll help you sort it out.
